# create a list of our conditions
conditions = [
    (df['weekday'] == 0),
    (df['weekday'] == 1),
    (df['weekday'] == 2), 
    (df['weekday'] == 3),
    (df['weekday'] == 4),
    (df['weekday'] == 5),
    (df['weekday'] == 6),
    ]

# create a list of the values we want to assign for each condition
values = ['Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 'Thursday', 'Friday', 'Saturday', 'Sunday']

# create a new column and use np.select to assign values to it using our lists as arguments
df['Day of Week'] = np.select(conditions, values)

# Weibull Distribution
from scipy.stats import weibull_min 
plt.hist(df["Charging_Time_As_Hours"], bins=100, density=True, alpha=0.5) 
shape, loc, scale = weibull_min.fit(df["Charging_Time_As_Hours"], floc=0) 
x = np.linspace(df["Charging_Time_As_Hours"].min(), df["Charging_Time_As_Hours"].max(), 100) 
plt.plot(x, weibull_min(shape, loc, scale).pdf(x)) 
plt.title("Weibull fit on ChargeTime data") 
plt.xlabel("ChargeTime")
